      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model selection and contact formulation justified by literature and sensitivity analysis; bilinear isotropic hardening demonstrated adequate for Ti-6Al-4V under monotonic loading.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (BISO) constitutive model selected for Ti-6Al-4V ELI based on published validation studies (Nagaraja 2019, Goel 2011). Augmented Lagrange contact formulation used for screw-rod and screw-block interfaces. Sensitivity analysis showed <3% QoI sensitivity to friction coefficient in range 0.15–0.35."
