      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span at least two load levels or loading rates to characterise response variability.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at single load configuration per ASTM F1717 (5° compression-bending, 10 mm/min crosshead speed). Only one test condition evaluated; requirement for Gradation 2 not met. This is a documented gap acknowledged in the credibility assessment; risk accepted given strong agreement at the tested condition and the regulatory precedent for single-condition F1717 submissions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to test article and test setup within quantified tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FEA geometry derived from CAD nominal with CMM-verified offsets. Fixture stiffness measured (48.2 kN/mm) and incorporated as spring boundary condition. Torque pre-load on set screws measured (4.0 Nm) and applied as pre-stress step. Equivalency confirmed for all three QoIs within ±5% of experimental mean prior to formal comparison."
    },
    {
